- Timeline and indicators: 6–12 months for legislative changes and implementation; indicators: tax-to-GDP ratio, VAT compliance rate, subsidy outlays as % of GDP, deficit trajectory.
- Risks/opposition and mitigations: Business groups may resist tax changes; mitigate with transitional relief for SMEs, sunset clauses, and broad-based communication on equity and growth rationale.
- Trade-offs: Short-term revenue volatility vs. longer-term fiscal sustainability and investment capacity.
- Contingency: If tax reform stalls, expand targeted revenue enforcement and postpone broader base-broadening until revenue flows stabilize.

